---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="About Me">
  <div class="page-container">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header">
        <h1 class="page-title">About Me</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          Software developer passionate about collaboration and craftsmanship
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-content">
        <div class="about-section">
          <h2>Hello, I'm Antony</h2>
          <p>
            I'm a software developer with a passion for creating meaningful
            digital experiences and contributing to open source projects.
            Currently, I'm working on the Fedora project for three months,
            focusing on improving user experience and system reliability.
          </p>
          <p>
            My journey in software development has taken me through various
            technologies and projects, from building web applications to
            contributing to Linux distributions. I believe in writing clean,
            maintainable code and sharing knowledge with the community.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
          <h2>Collaboration & Craftsmanship</h2>
          <p>
            I believe great software is built through collaboration. Whether
            working with open source communities or development teams, I bring a
            collaborative spirit and attention to detail that ensures quality
            outcomes. My approach combines technical expertise with strong
            communication skills.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every project I work on reflects my commitment to craftsmanship. I
            take pride in writing code that is not only functional but also
            elegant, maintainable, and well-documented. This attention to detail
            extends to user experience design and system architecture.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
          <h2>Current Focus</h2>
          <p>
            I'm currently dedicating my time to the Fedora project, where I'm
            working on package management improvements and user interface
            enhancements. This experience has deepened my understanding of Linux
            systems and open source development practices.
          </p>
          <p>
            The collaborative nature of open source development has taught me
            valuable lessons about code review, community engagement, and the
            importance of clear communication in distributed teams.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
          <h2>Experience & Skills</h2>
          <p>
            Over the years, I've worked on various projects ranging from
            enterprise applications to personal hobby projects. My experience
            spans web development, system programming, and user interface
            design. I enjoy tackling complex problems and finding elegant
            solutions.
          </p>
          <div class="skills-grid">
            <div class="skill-category">
              <h3>Frontend</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Vue & Nuxt</li>
                <li>React & Next.js</li>
                <li>TypeScript</li>
                <li>Modern CSS</li>
                <li>UI/UX Design</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="skill-category">
              <h3>Backend</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Node.js</li>
                <li>Python</li>
                <li>PostgreSQL</li>
                <li>API Design</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="skill-category">
              <h3>Tools & Systems</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Git & GitHub</li>
                <li>Linux Systems</li>
                <li>Docker</li>
                <li>CI/CD</li>
                <li>AWS</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
          <h2>Philosophy</h2>
          <p>
            I believe in the power of clean code and thoughtful design. Less is
            often more, and I strive to create solutions that are both
            functional and beautiful. Open source software has shaped my career,
            and I'm committed to giving back to the community.
          </p>
          <p>
            Collaboration isn't just about working with othersâ€”it's about
            creating an environment where everyone can contribute their best
            work. I value diverse perspectives and believe that the best
            solutions emerge from inclusive, collaborative processes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
